    • read

      public T read(DataInputStream inputStream, int bytesLeft) throws IOException
      Reads data from , verifies it with the matcher (if it was set) and returns the result (if it is valid).
      Parameters:
      inputStream - the stream which is used to read the bytes from
      bytesLeft - the total number of bytes left on the stream to read
      Returns:
      null if a matcher exists and succeeded. if no matcher is set, the value read from the stream is returned
      Throws:
      IOException - if the matcher failed
